race.comment: FAGES (2) produced a modest effort most recently when fifth at this track over 520m behind Bad Boy Red (30.75) in a Grade 6. Was in the money the start prior. Some good form is emerging from his last run. Can atone. SIR GIDEON (5) had won two in a row before finishing second (30.46) last time at this track. Comes through a solid form race last start. Expected to be in this for a long way. FILL MY POCKETS (1) jumps from box 1 again after placing (35.58) last time at this track over 600m. Has the ability and looks a key chance. TOTE DEOR (3) raced on the pace and got home last start. Big chance on that form.
